            "subject": "LU-7734 lnet: peer/peer_ni handling adjustments"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Amir Shehata",
          "email": "amir.shehata@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-06-09 06:08:06.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Amir Shehata",
          "email": "amir.shehata@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-06-14 20:40:11.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-7734 lnet: proper cpt locking",
        "message": "LU-7734 lnet: proper cpt locking\n\n1. add a per NI credits, which is just the total credits\n   assigned on NI creation\n2. Whenever percpt credits are added or decremented, we\n   mirror that in the NI credits\n3. We use the NI credits to determine best NI\n4. After we have completed the peer_ni/ni selection we\n   determine the cpt to use for locking:\n\tcpt_of_nid(lpni->nid, ni)\n\nThe lpni_cpt is not enough to protect all the fields in the\nlnet_peer_ni structure. This is due to the fact that multiple\nNIs can talk to the same peer, and functions can be called with\ndifferent cpts locked. To properly protect the fields in the\nlnet_peer_ni structure, a spin lock is introduced for the\npurpose.\n\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <amir.shehata@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ief7868c3c8ff7e00ea9e908dd50d8cef77d9f9a4\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/20701\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/multi-rail"
    }
  },
